ViCell Cell Linking Exception
Version 1.0, June 2026

This Exception is an additional permission under the Mozilla Public License
2.0 (MPL-2.0) as applied to the ViCell Standard Runtime ("ostd") located
at libs/ostd/ in the ViCell repository.

DEFINITIONS
-----------

"ViCell Standard Runtime" refers to the software in libs/ostd/.

"Cell" means a self-contained software unit compiled independently from
the ViCell Standard Runtime that interacts with ViCell ONLY through the
public interfaces declared in libs/api/ (ABI traits) and the public API
of the ViCell Standard Runtime, and does not incorporate source code
copied from MPL-2.0 covered files.

"Single Address Space (SAS)" means the runtime model in which one or more
Cells and the ViCell kernel share a single virtual address space, with
isolation provided by the Rust type system (Language-Based Isolation, LBI)
rather than hardware memory management unit (MMU) boundaries.

GRANT OF EXCEPTION
------------------

Subject to the terms and conditions of the MPL-2.0, you are granted a
special permission to convey a Cell that:

  (a) links statically or dynamically against the ViCell Standard Runtime,
  (b) is loaded into the same virtual address space as the ViCell kernel,
  (c) communicates with the ViCell kernel and Standard Runtime ONLY through
      the public interfaces in libs/api/ and the public API of ostd/,

under terms of your choosing, without such linking, loading, or address-space
co-residence causing the Cell to be considered "Covered Software" or part of
a "Larger Work" under the MPL-2.0, PROVIDED THAT the Cell does not
incorporate any source code copied from MPL-2.0 covered files.

CLARIFICATION ON SAS AND DERIVED WORKS
---------------------------------------

The fact that a Cell and the ViCell kernel share a virtual address space,
or that the ViCell loader performs relocation placing Cell code in memory
adjacent to kernel code, does NOT, by itself, make a Cell a derivative work
of the ViCell Standard Runtime or the ViCell kernel under any applicable
copyright law.

The isolation of Cells via the Rust type system (Language-Based Isolation)
is treated by all parties as legally equivalent, for purposes of determining
derivative work status, to process isolation in conventional operating
systems (as recognized in the Linux kernel syscall exception and the FSF's
guidance on GPL and operating system interfaces).

CONDITIONS AND LIMITS
---------------------

This Exception does NOT apply if:

  1. The Cell incorporates source code copied or adapted from MPL-2.0
     covered files (e.g., copy-pasting ostd internals into a Cell). In
     that case, the copied portions remain MPL-2.0 covered.

  2. The Cell is a modification of the ViCell Standard Runtime itself.
     Such modifications remain MPL-2.0 covered.

  3. The Cell communicates with the kernel through mechanisms other than
     the declared public ABI (e.g., direct memory manipulation of kernel
     data structures, unsafe pointer casts to kernel types not in
     libs/api/).

INTENT
------

The intent of this Exception is to ensure that:

  1. The ViCell Standard Runtime (ostd) remains open — modifications to
     ostd must be shared back under MPL-2.0.

  2. Applications built on top of ViCell using the public ABI can be
     distributed under any license the author chooses, including
     proprietary licenses, without legal ambiguity arising from the SAS
     architecture.

  3. ViCell can build a diverse ecosystem of applications including
     commercial software, matching the practical freedoms available to
     application developers on conventional operating systems.

